body:
@inutano  I am delighted to discover ChIP-Atlas.  Here at the Institute for Systems Biology I work on Bioconductor packages (trena, trenaViz, MotifDb, ...)  all of which are complementary to the data you provide, and will become stronger as a result.

I wonder if the the helpful user interface you provide  https://chip-atlas.org/peak_browser could be extended so that one can specify a genomic region (for instance hg38 or hg19 chr2:127,015,600-127,181,721) to constrain the query?     This would allow us to obtain a small bed file quickly.

Forgive me if this constraint is already provided and I overlooked it.

## Target genes

```
exp-targetGene (relation) a :PutativeRegulation ;
  :hasTF (TF, ensembl gene) ;
  :hasTarget (target gene, ensembl gene);
  :score1k <value>;
  :score5k <value>;
  :score10k <value>;
  :hasExperiment (experiment) ;
  :hasCellLine (cell line) .
```

## Colocalization

```
exp-exp (relation) a :Colocalization ;
  :hasTF (TF) ;
  :hasPartner (TF) ;
  :hasExperiment (experiment) ;
  :hasPartnerExp (experiment) ;
  :coloScore <value, string?> ;
  :hasCellLine (cell line) ;
  :hasPartnerCellLine (cell line) .
```

cc. @sh-ikeda @hchiba1
